The paper deals with a specific subclass of Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) and proposes algorithms for its resolution. This makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also uses graph-based proofs and hypergraph closure, which are common techniques in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the tractability of the problem, which is a topic that falls under the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
